@Rusty
Just imagine its a movie instead of a game.
BAM! No more reason to feel so upset.

@Logan Miles
Something I liked most about the game was a supernatural story which didn't involve religion, and kept everything pretty tidy and quasi-scientific. Usually when something has supernatural elements in it all logic goes out the window because "spirits can do whatever". But this game kept the experience more real by giving the spirit world rules and regulations much like we have.

Also the voice acting is incredible in many places.

@bulbinking
"supernatural story which didn't involve religion,"
Actually, the ghosts in S:TS were linked up with the Novajos, so yah...

@TheGrowthCycle
Yes, but in many supernatural games they either don't explain the spirits at all or go the whole "all fairytales are true" route which is lazy and causes even more confusion.

BTS took a more "scientific" and even naturalistic approach to the game.
